statement.p:
Let D be a domain in \mathbb{R}^m, E a domain in \mathbb{R}^n, and \mb{G} : D \to E is a smooth differentiable function. If \nu and \eta are differential forms on E then


 \mb{G}^* (\eta \wedge \nu) = (\mb{G}^* \eta ) \wedge (\mb{G}^* \nu ) 

  \mb{G}^* \, \tder{}{\eta} = \tder{}{\mb{G}^* \eta }
